# 🎊 Nigerian Celebrity Wedding News Scraper

## Project Overview
An automated n8n workflow that scrapes Google News every week for Nigerian celebrity wedding stories, extracts article details and images, and saves everything automatically to a Google Sheet for easy reference and analysis.

---

## What This Workflow Does
1. **Triggers automatically** every Monday morning via Schedule Trigger
2. **Fetches Nigerian celebrity wedding news** from Google News RSS feed
3. **Loops through each article** one at a time
4. **Extracts the article title, link, published date, and image URL** using JavaScript
5. **Packages the data** into a clean structured format
6. **Saves each story** as a new row in Google Sheets automatically

---

## Tools and Technologies Used
- **n8n** (self-hosted, v2.19.4)
- **Google News RSS Feed** (no API key required)
- **JavaScript Code Nodes** (data extraction and transformation)
- **Google Sheets API** (data storage)

---

## Workflow Nodes
| Node | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Schedule Trigger | Runs every Monday at 8AM |
| HTTP Request | Fetches Google News RSS feed |
| XML | Converts RSS XML to JSON |
| Code in JavaScript | Extracts article titles and links |
| Loop Over Items | Processes one article at a time |
| HTTP Request 1 | Fetches full article HTML content |
| Code in JavaScript 1 | Extracts relevant image URL |
| Wait | Pauses 5 seconds between requests |
| Code in JavaScript 2 | Packages all data for Google Sheets |
| Append Row in Sheet | Saves data to Google Sheets |

---

## Google Sheets Output Structure
| Column | Data |
|---|---|
| Title | Article headline |
| Couple Names | See article |
| Wedding Date | See article |
| Venue | See article |
| Summary | Short description |
| Source URL | Link to full article |
| Date Scraped | Date workflow ran |
| Image URL | Main image from article |

---

## RSS Feed Used
```
https://news.google.com/rss/search?q=Nigerian+celebrity+wedding&hl=en-NG&gl=NG&ceid=NG:en
```

---

## How to Use This Workflow
1. Import the JSON file into your n8n instance
2. Create a Google Sheet with the column headers above
3. Connect your Google Sheets credential
4. Activate the workflow
5. It will run automatically every Monday

